
Python - Django rest framework

1. Create a virtual environment
   --> Install Python 3.x from https://www.python.org/downloads/ and add it to PATH (Environment Variables -> System Variables -> Path)

   **  py -3 -m venv .venv **

2. Activate the virtual environment
    --> Open a new command prompt

    ** .venv\Scripts\activate **

3. Install the required packages
    pip install django
    pip install djangorestframework

4. Create a new Django project
    django-admin startproject DjangoProject

5. Create a new app
    cd DjangoProject
    python manage.py startapp userInfo

6. Create a new model
    cd userInfo
    1. create class for the model and add the fields for database table

7.  migration
    python manage.py makemigrations
    python manage.py migrate

8. Create a new serializer
    serializer for the model

9. update view.py for the api

10. create a url.py for the app api and it will be add to project urls.py

11. run the server
    python manage.py runserver
